<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en">
<head>
  <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=UTF-8" />
  <title>cortito - URL shortener by akosma software</title>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'scaffold' %>
</head>
<body>
    
<h1>cortito - URL shortener by <a href="http://akosma.com">akosma software</a></h1>

<%= yield %>

<hr />

<p><strong>Bookmarklet for your browser:</strong> <%= link_to "shorten with cortito", "javascript:location.href='http://" + @host + "/?url='+encodeURIComponent(location.href);" %> (drag and drop on your bookmark toolbar)</p>

<p><strong>API:</strong> send a POST or GET request to <tt><%= @host %></tt> with a "url" parameter, with either an "Accept: application/javascript" or "Accept: text/xml" header. You'll get a simple text response with the shortened URL.</p>

<hr />

<p>Powered by <a href="http://akosma.com">akosma software</a>&apos;s <a href="http://github.com/akosma/cortito/">cortito <%= CORTITO_VERSION %></a></p>

</body>
</html>
